Send different SOAP requests stored in flat files (like XML) to the CurrencyConverter web service using SoapUI's DataSource TestStep.

ğŸ” Step-by-Step Process:
1ï¸âƒ£ Create a SoapUI Project
Go to SoapUI â†’ File â†’ New SOAP Project

Use the WSDL:

http://www.webservicex.com/CurrencyConvertor.asmx?wsdl
2ï¸âƒ£ Create a TestSuite and TestCase
Right-click the project â†’ New TestSuite

Inside TestSuite â†’ New TestCase

3ï¸âƒ£ Add a DataSource TestStep
In your TestCase editor â†’ Click Add Step â†’ DataSource

Choose DataSource Type = Directory

4ï¸âƒ£ Configure the Directory Settings
In the DataSource configuration:

Set Directory path where your .xml or .txt request files are stored

Set Filter:

For XML: *.xml

For Text: *.txt

Encoding: Default is fine unless your files use a specific one

Under Property, enter a name (e.g. RequestData)
(This will hold the contents of each file)

ğŸ”¹ Note: If you name the property Filename, it will store the file name instead of its content.

5ï¸âƒ£ Add a SOAP Request TestStep
Click Add Step â†’ Test Request

Choose ConversionRate operation from CurrencyConverterSoap interface

Press OK â†’ XML editor opens

6ï¸âƒ£ Link the SOAP Request with DataSource
Delete the existing XML content in the request editor

Right-click â†’ Choose Insert Property â†’ DataSource â†’ RequestData

This will insert something like:


${DataSource#RequestData}
This tells SoapUI to use the request content from each flat file

ğŸ”¸ Tip: If an XPATH window appears while inserting, just click OK without selecting anything.

7ï¸âƒ£ Add DataSource Loop
Add a DataSource Loop TestStep

Source Step: DataSource

Target Step: SOAP Request

End Step: (last step before loop restarts)

âœ… Example XML in Input File
xml
<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:web="http://www.webserviceX.NET/">
   <soapenv:Header/>
   <soapenv:Body>
      <web:ConversionRate>
         <web:FromCurrency>SEK</web:FromCurrency>
         <web:ToCurrency>USD</web:ToCurrency>
      </web:ConversionRate>
   </soapenv:Body>
</soapenv:Envelope>
ğŸ§ª Execution
Run the TestCase â†’ SoapUI will:

Pick each file from the folder

Extract its content

Use it as the request

Send it to the web service

Repeat for all files

